The SABC’s financial certainty still hangs in the balance. Addressing Parliament’s Communication Portfolio Committee, Communications Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams said the National Treasury has rejected the cash-strapped public broadcaster’s turnaround strategy. The SABC is seeking a R6.8 billion government guarantee. There are still fears about the possible arrival of Day Zero when the broadcaster will not be able to pay salaries. Ndabeni-Abrahams says the SABC’s financial challenges are as a result of what she terms over-bloated staff. Watch the Minister’s full address… 